<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-01-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="826" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d826">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-01-11"><hi rend="italic">January 11,
                                1897</hi></date>. (Received Jan. 25.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1135.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that
                            Missionary Cole, at Bitlis, telegraphed me requesting the withdrawal of
                            the Turkish guard at that place. I have had telegraphic orders sent
                            complying with his request as you were informed by telegram, a copy of
                            which I append on the overleaf.</p>
                        <p>No reasons were given by Mr. Cole for wishing to dispense with a
                            guard.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>